Happy 1 Year of Snackvivor!

We truly cannot thank everyone here enough for all the amazing times we have had as a community. It is hard to believe how fast the time has gone by, but exactly one year ago to the minute, we set off for Cheeseland! Since then it has been nothing but incredible people coming together to laugh, love, cry, and all the other things we have done in Snackvivor. It has been so wonderful to see everyone rally behind the community and support each other, I can't wait for year two of Snackvivor because it is going to be even more of all the great things we have already done together. And on a personal note, I'm so grateful for all the people here in this community. When I stumbled into ORGs about a year and a half ago, I never thought they would have had as big of an impact on my life as they do. After playing my first ORG and experiencing the magic, I wanted to recreate that for so many more people. I'm so lucky for this hosting team, current and past, they are the best friends in the world and have brought me so much happiness and joy over the past year. I have so many great memories and I'm so thankful I get to call them my family. And to all our players and spectators, thank you for joining us on this journey and allowing us to be a great community. You are all the reason this place is so special and every day you continue to show how great the Snackvivor community is. So here is to many more years of Snackvivor! We have so much to celebrate (and a few surprises to do just that), so once again happy one year to Snackvivor!
